		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.webhostingshow.com/?p=4042</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Does your web site have a terms of service or privacy policy?&#160; Now, there are many web sites on the Web that really do not require these two documents to be posted, but there are many that could be helped by getting these legal terms posted too.&#160; To help you out I have found a [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Does your web site have a terms of service or privacy policy?&nbsp; Now, there are many web sites on the Web that really do not require these two documents to be posted, but there are many that could be helped by getting these legal terms posted too.&nbsp; To help you out I have found a place that will help you generate both for your own web site or business, for no cost to you.</p>
<p><span id="more-4042"></span>
<p><strong>Get Your Legal Documentation Done Easily!</strong>
<p>Once you load up the legal document builders, they are very easy to use.&nbsp; An online entrepreneur only needs to fill out the basics about their web site or business, and the web site wizard takes care of the rest of the work.
<p>Once you are done, the documents you need are returned to you via the Internet automatically, along with an HTML version of the code, so you can easily post it into your own web site’s pages.
<p>You can check out both tools here:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://privacy-policy-generator.legalriver.com/">Privacy Policy Generator</a>
<li><a href="http://terms-of-service-generator.legalriver.com/">Terms of Service Generator</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Having a good set of legal documentation on your web site to cover your assets is a good thing to go ahead and get covered.&nbsp; Now, I am far from a lawyer, nor do I play one on the Internet, however Legal River seems to be willing to help with these two form builders to get you pointed in the right direction when it comes to setting up a privacy policy or a terms of service agreement.</p>
